<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5824&amp;p=29232#p29232"><![CDATA[
Only start menu skins here. No themes. Themes alter the whole look of the system.<br /><br />The latest version of Classic Shell Menu can have some texture on the taskbar, <br />along with blur/transparency settings.<br />To get exact look of Windows 7, with a theme on Win 10, might not even be possible.<br />Microsoft has taken a lot of theme capability away, and the blur is not same type.<br /><br />Win7 has got to be the best looking system, Microsoft ever made. <br />Their taskbar buttons with all the luscious animated lighting effects, so beautiful. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> <br />Best way to enjoy Win7 is have the real thing.<br /><br />The best we can do here, is add an image for the task bar. <br />Will still have the bland Win 10 square buttons on the taskbar, though. <br /><br />You can look in the taskbar forum section for various types of taskbar images for Win7 look.<br />To make it easy, here are a couple from that section. I put them in a zip.<br />Unzip and put the two images somewhere that won't get deleted easily, like picture folder.<br /><br />You need to set it up in the taskbar settings tab.<br />After pointing to location of one of taskbar images, set to Horizontal stretching,<br />and Vertical stretching with Border sizes 2,0<br /><br /><br />The &quot;Win7 simple taskbar.png&quot; can be used for menu medium option, <br />with CSM settings Menu look tab-Glass opacity at default 50<br />and Taskbar tab-Taskbar opacity at default 85<br /><br />For a closer look, use the wider image &quot;Win7 Taskbar Reflection for opacity 40 qty .png&quot;<br />Set menu skin to Low glass color option. Set menu Glass opacity to 30,<br />and taskbar opacity to 40.<br /><br />If you are using Win 8, there is no blur available, I'm not sure what settings work.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Wed Sep 07, 2016 7:45 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
